        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Switzerland offers L permits (short-term, up to 1 year), B permits (residence, 1-5 years), G permits (cross-border commuters), and C permits (permanent settlement, after 5-10 years). EU/EFTA nationals have easier access, while third-country nationals need employer sponsorship subject to quotas."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long does it take to get a Swiss work permit?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Processing times vary by nationality and permit type. EU/EFTA nationals can usually register within 2-4 weeks. Third-country nationals typically wait 6-12 weeks for work permit approval. Applications must be submitted before starting employment."
      }
