            <p class="text-xl lg:text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Need Help with Swiss Immigration?</p>
            <p class="text-white/90 mb-4 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Get expert guidance on work permits, residence permits, and family reunification. Our immigration specialists help expats navigate Switzerland's visa requirements.</p>
            <button 
              onclick="universalOpenModal({page: 'immigration_service', service: 'immigration'})"
              class="inline-flex items-center justify-center bg-white text-primary-700 px-8 py-4 rounded-xl font-semibold hover:bg-gray-50 transition-all duration-300 hover:scale-105 shadow-lg"
            >
              Get a Free Consultation with our Preferred Partner
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"/>
              </svg>
            </button>
            <p class="text-xs text-white/70 mt-3">Our relocation partners work with us and provide free consultations to all users</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Why Immigration Is a Major Challenge -->
        <div class="mb-16">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Why Immigration Is a Major Challenge for Expats</h2>
          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
            <p>
              Switzerland's immigration system is known for its <strong>strict regulations and complex procedures</strong>. The requirements 
              differ significantly between EU/EFTA nationals and third-country nationals, with varying permit types, quotas, and processing 
              times. Understanding which visa or permit applies to your situation is crucial for a successful Swiss relocation.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong>Cantonal authorities</strong> handle most immigration matters, meaning procedures can vary across 
              <a href="/locations/zurich" class="text-primary-600 hover:underline">Zurich</a>, 
              <a href="/locations/geneva" class="text-primary-600 hover:underline">Geneva</a>, 
              <a href="/locations/basel" class="text-primary-600 hover:underline">Basel</a>, and 
              <a href="/locations/bern" class="text-primary-600 hover:underline">Bern</a>. Each canton has specific requirements 
              for work permits, residence permits, and family reunification. Third-country nationals face annual quotas that limit the 
              number of permits issued, making timing and proper documentation critical.
            </p>
