                requirements due to its international organizations and diplomatic community. <strong>Special visa categories</strong> exist 
                for UN employees, NGO workers, and diplomatic families. Geneva's immigration office handles high volumes of international 
                applications with specific documentation requirements. Our specialists navigate these specialized procedures and provide 
                family-focused immigration support for expatriate communities in this international hub.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Basel Immigration Services</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                <a href="/locations/basel" class="text-primary-600 hover:underline font-medium">Basel</a> offers 
                <strong>EU cross-border permits (G permits)</strong> for workers living in neighboring countries. The pharmaceutical 
                and life sciences industry drives significant work permit demand. Basel's proximity to France and Germany creates unique 
                immigration scenarios requiring specialized knowledge. Our immigration experts handle both standard residence permits and 
                complex cross-border arrangements for pharmaceutical industry expats.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
