              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Section -->
        <div class="mb-16">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">FAQ – Swiss Immigration</h2>
          <div class="space-y-6">
            
            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-md transition">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">What types of permits are available for expats in Switzerland?</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                Switzerland offers several permit types: <strong>L permits</strong> (short-term residence, up to 1 year, renewable), 
                <strong>B permits</strong> (residence permit, 1-5 years based on employment), <strong>G permits</strong> (cross-border 
                commuter permit for those living in neighboring countries), and <strong>C permits</strong> (permanent settlement after 
                5-10 years continuous residence). EU/EFTA nationals have easier access to all permit types, while third-country nationals 
                need employer sponsorship and are subject to annual quotas. Our immigration specialists help determine which permit applies 
                to your situation.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-md transition">
